TECH_PARAM_1.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Date of the beginning of buoyancy reduction (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_2.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Day number of the beginning of buoyancy reduction (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_3.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Date of the beginning of buoyancy reduction (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_4.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Duration of the basic valve actions.

TECH_PARAM_5.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of solenoid valve actions at the surface until the crossing of the GAP threshold

TECH_PARAM_6.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Grounding at surface (0 : no grounding, 1 : grounding)
TECH_PARAM_6.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: is the float beached? - could be logical

TECH_PARAM_8.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when first stabilization appears during descent to park (tenths of an hour since midnight)

TECH_PARAM_9.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when park pressure is reached  (tenths of an hour since midnight)

TECH_PARAM_10.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Nb of valve actions in descent to parking depth
TECH_PARAM_10.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_11.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Nb of pump actions in descent to parking depth
TECH_PARAM_11.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_12.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when park pressure is reached

TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Nb of entrance in drift target range (descent)
TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: descent to park pressure: number of entries in margin around park pressure target - specifically, how many times the float enters the band of pressure surrounding the target park pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Nb of repositionning during drift at parking depth
TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of times the float readjusts its buoyancy during park phase - using either the pump or EV

TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions during drift at parking depth
TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions during park phase

TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions during drift at parking depth
TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions while at park depth

TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Descent to profile depth start time
TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of minutes elapsed in the day at the beginning of the descent to profile depth.

TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Descent to profile depth end time
TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of minutes elapsed in the day at the end of the descent to profile depth.

TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Nb of valve actions during descent to profile depth
TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions during descent to start profile pressure

TECH_PARAM_20.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Nb of pump actions during descent to profile depth
TECH_PARAM_20.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions during descent to start profile pressure

TECH_PARAM_21.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of entrance in profile target range
TECH_PARAM_21.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: descent to profile pressure: number of entries in margin around profile pressure target  - specifically, how many times the float enters the band of pressure surrounding the target profile pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_22.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of repositionning in profile stand-by
TECH_PARAM_22.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: at profile pressure stand-by, number of times the float readjusts its buoyancy - using either the pump or EV

TECH_PARAM_23.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions during drift at profile depth
TECH_PARAM_23.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions while drifting at profile depth

TECH_PARAM_24.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions during drift at profile depth
TECH_PARAM_24.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of pump actions during drift at profile depth.

TECH_PARAM_26.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time of the first transmission for this cycle

TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions in ascent
TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions between start and end of ascent

TECH_PARAM_28.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Surface pressure recorded just before the previous descent but data is corrected on board the float. Note: cumulative NEGATIVE   offset  (real offset * -1) but no further correction required. Autocorrected

TECH_PARAM_30.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery voltage drop at Pmax, pump ON (with regards to Unom = 15.0 V, in dV)

TECH_PARAM_31.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: real time clock status - 1= OK, 0=not OK

TECH_PARAM_33.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Oxygen sensor status (0 : ok, 1 : problem, 2 : none)
TECH_PARAM_33.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag indicating the status of the Optode (see manual)

TECH_PARAM_34.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: GPS valid fix (1 = valid, 0 = not valid)
TECH_PARAM_34.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag for GPS fix determination (1 if a valid fix has been transmitted in tech msg, 0 otherwise).

TECH_PARAM_35.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: the number of seconds required to obtain a GPS fix for a profile

TECH_PARAM_36.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Pump duration (buoyancy retrieve for GPS acquisition)
TECH_PARAM_36.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: duration of additional pump actions at the surface performed during GPS acquisition in case of insufficient buoyancy

TECH_PARAM_37.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag indicating the status of the antenna (see manual)

TECH_PARAM_38.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Clock time when End of Life mode starts

TECH_PARAM_39.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the descent phases (from surface to the parking depth and from the parking depth to the profile depth).

TECH_PARAM_40.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the drift at park depth.

TECH_PARAM_41.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface.

TECH_PARAM_42.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of CTD near surface packets
TECH_PARAM_42.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the near surface measurement phase.

TECH_PARAM_43.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of CTD in air packets
TECH_PARAM_43.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the in air measurement phase.

TECH_PARAM_44.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of descent slices in shallow zone
TECH_PARAM_44.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Descending profile reduction Number of slices in shallow zone - NTS

TECH_PARAM_45.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of descent slices in deep zone
TECH_PARAM_45.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Descending profile reduction Number of slices in deep zone - NTF

TECH_PARAM_46.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of CTD measurements in drift

TECH_PARAM_47.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of ascent slices in shallow zone
TECH_PARAM_47.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Ascending profile reduction Number of slices in shallow zone - NTS

TECH_PARAM_48.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of ascent slices in deep zone
TECH_PARAM_48.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Ascending profile reduction Number of slices in deep zone - NTF

TECH_PARAM_49.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of CTD near surface measurements

TECH_PARAM_50.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of CTD in air measurements

TECH_PARAM_51.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Last (shallowest) pumped raw pressure sample acquired during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface (i.e. just before the cut-off pressure where the pump is stopped) (in dbars).

TECH_PARAM_52.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: grounded flag , diagnostic bit - could also be logical?  Yes/no? 0/1? Or can be number of profiles during which the float grounded

TECH_PARAM_53.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: 1st grounding day relative to cycle start
TECH_PARAM_53.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Day number when the float grounds for the first time (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_55.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: 1st Grounding phase (buoyancy reduction: 2, descent to parking pressure: 3, drift at parking depth: 4, descent to profile pressure: 5, drift at profile depth: 6)
TECH_PARAM_55.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Phase of the float life or cycle when the first grounding occurred.  See the manual for phase definition - this will vary with float type

TECH_PARAM_56.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of ev activations before 1st grounding detection
TECH_PARAM_56.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of valve actions done at constant pressure to set the grounded flag for the first grounding event

TECH_PARAM_57.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: 2nd grounding day relative to cycle start
TECH_PARAM_57.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Day number when the float grounds for the first time (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_59.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: 2nd Grounding phase (buoyancy reduction: 2, descent to parking pressure: 3, drift at parking depth: 4, descent to profile pressure: 5, drift at profile depth: 6)
TECH_PARAM_59.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Phase of the float life or cycle when the second grounding occurred.  See the manual for phase definition - this will vary with float type

TECH_PARAM_60.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of ev activations before 2nd grounding detection
TECH_PARAM_60.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of valve actions done at constant pressure to set the grounded flag for the second grounding event

TECH_PARAM_61.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Emergency ascents - Internal count

TECH_PARAM_62.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of minutes elapsed in the day of the float first emergency ascent.

TECH_PARAM_63.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Pressure that triggered the first emergency ascent

TECH_PARAM_64.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Emergency ascent - pump actions at emergency depth

TECH_PARAM_65.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: 1st emergency ascent relative day (to 1st cycle day)
TECH_PARAM_65.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Day number of the float first emergency ascent (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_66.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control successfully considered.

TECH_PARAM_67.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control rejected by the float (due to out of range value or remote control syntax error).

TECH_PARAM_68.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control commands successfully considered.

TECH_PARAM_69.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control commands rejected by the float.

TECH_PARAM_70.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Duration on the previous Iridium session

TECH_PARAM_71.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of SBD session for reception
TECH_PARAM_71.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Incoming Iridium Messages Received during previous session

TECH_PARAM_72.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of SBD session for transmission
TECH_PARAM_72.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Incoming Iridium Messages Sent during previous session

TECH_PARAM_73.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Pump actions before float begins ascent
TECH_PARAM_73.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of pump actions needed to start the ascent.

TECH_PARAM_74.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Internal tube pressure [mbar] in profile depth

TECH_PARAM_75.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Clock time of the last reset of the float

TECH_PARAM_76.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Auto-test is performed at the beginning of the mission: Flag 0 = Problem, 1 = OK

TECH_PARAM_77.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Detailed auto-test for float hardware resulting in a detailed code for each tested sub-part (see manual)

TECH_PARAM_78.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Software check on the float memory contents (0 if problems were found and 1 if no problem occured)

TECH_PARAM_79.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: External bladder state at deployment (0: float stay at surface, 1: heavy float at deployment)

TECH_PARAM_80.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: CTD status (0 : no error, 1: fast pressure default time-out, 2: fast pressure broken frame, 16: CTD default time-out, 32: CTD broken frame)
TECH_PARAM_80.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag indicating the status of the CTD (see manual) (could be reported as hex)

TECH_PARAM_81.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Float phase during CTD default detection
TECH_PARAM_81.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Phase of the float life or cycle when the CTD occurred.  See the manual for phase definition - this will vary with float type

TECH_PARAM_82.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of descent CTD packets received
TECH_PARAM_82.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets received to transmit sensor data collected during the descent phases (from surface to the parking depth and from the parking depth to the profile depth).

TECH_PARAM_83.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of drift CTD packets received
TECH_PARAM_83.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets received to transmit sensor data collected during the drift at park depth.

TECH_PARAM_84.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of ascent CTD packets received
TECH_PARAM_84.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets received to transmit sensor data collected during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface.

TECH_PARAM_85.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of CTD near surface packets received
TECH_PARAM_85.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets received to transmit sensor data collected during the near surface measurement phase.

TECH_PARAM_86.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of CTD in air packets received
TECH_PARAM_86.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets received to transmit sensor data collected during the in air measurement phase.

TECH_PARAM_87.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets received to transmit hydraulic data recorded during the cycle.

TECH_PARAM_88.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of times technical message #1 has been received.

TECH_PARAM_89.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of times technical message #2 has been received.

TECH_PARAM_90.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of times parameter message has been received.
